        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 15 at 7:02PM EDT until July 15 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>SVRGSP

The National Weather Service in Greenville-Spartanburg has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Alexander County in the Piedmont of North Carolina...
Northern Iredell County in the Piedmont of North Carolina...

* Until 800 PM EDT.

* At 702 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles northeast
of Statesville, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

* Locations impacted include...
Statesville, Harmony, Love Valley, Turnersburg, Olin, Union Grove,
Scotts, and Cool Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.

Please report damaging winds, hail, or flooding to the National
Weather Service by calling toll free, 1, 800, 2 6 7, 8 1 0 1, or by
posting on our Facebook page, or post it to X using hashtag nwsgsp.
Your message should describe the event and the specific location
where it occurred.</instruction>
